parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Firestone Tire Tread Separation and Blowout
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected failure of Firestone tires can lead to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
A malfunctioning jack system can lead to accidents or injuries when attempting to change a tire, as the vehicle may not be properly supported, causing it to fall off the jack.
symptoms: The jack does not lift the vehicle correctly
the jack collapses or fails to hold the vehicle in place
the jack is difficult to operate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A poorly installed towing package can cause electrical system failures, leading to burnouts and potentially causing accidents or fires.
A failed air conditioner unit can cause discomfort and distraction while driving, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The air conditioner does not blow cold air
the air conditioner makes unusual noises
the air conditioner fails to turn on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air intake cover can cause debris to enter the engine, potentially leading to engine damage, decreased performance, and reduced fuel efficiency.
symptoms: Debris or dirt entering the engine

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fuel leak around the injector pump can cause a fire hazard, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: fuel droplets or leaks around the injector pump
